01:06:17.040 --> 01:06:20.210
And what one can
see is basically

01:06:20.210 --> 01:06:22.700
they perform differently.

01:06:22.700 --> 01:06:26.060
And what I'd like to do
is just examines what

01:06:26.060 --> 01:06:30.110
would have been an
optimal allocation

01:06:30.110 --> 01:06:33.980
across these exchange-traded
funds over this period.

01:06:33.980 --> 01:06:36.910
So basically looking
back at the data

01:06:36.910 --> 01:06:43.690
and seeing how our
portfolio analysis

01:06:43.690 --> 01:06:49.630
tools would result in particular
application allocations.

01:06:49.630 --> 01:06:53.370
So we can look at the
risk versus return

01:06:53.370 --> 01:06:54.890
annualized of these.

01:06:54.890 --> 01:07:09.610
Let's see-- this is-- I
guess that good enough.

01:07:09.610 --> 01:07:12.300
Anyway, what you can see
is a volatility range

01:07:12.300 --> 01:07:15.510
between 0 and 30.

01:07:15.510 --> 01:07:19.630
Annualized want return
between 0 and 25.

01:07:19.630 --> 01:07:23.880
We have the different
sectors in this plot.

01:07:23.880 --> 01:07:27.970
So this is our
feasible set-- this

01:07:27.970 --> 01:07:32.060
is the plot of return versus
volatility for these nine

01:07:32.060 --> 01:07:33.840
exchange-traded funds.

01:07:33.840 --> 01:07:35.820
This happens to be utilities.

01:07:35.820 --> 01:07:37.680
There's financials over there.

01:07:37.680 --> 01:07:39.450
Here's consumer staples.

01:07:39.450 --> 01:07:41.970
Very top is a consumer
discretionary.

01:07:50.780 --> 01:07:54.880
Let's see, I applied a
mean-variance optimization

01:07:54.880 --> 01:07:59.740
to this problem,
assuming that there's

01:07:59.740 --> 01:08:06.240
a constraint of 30% of
the capital per asset.

01:08:06.240 --> 01:08:07.970
So we don't want to
invest more than 30%

01:08:07.970 --> 01:08:12.080
of the capital in any
single exchange-traded fund.

01:08:12.080 --> 01:08:23.160
And this graph here shows how,
as we vary our target return

01:08:23.160 --> 01:08:25.340
from sort of the
minimum value up

01:08:25.340 --> 01:08:28.899
to the maximum value for
being fully invested,

01:08:28.899 --> 01:08:31.390
how much of the capital
we're going to invest

01:08:31.390 --> 01:08:34.005
in the different sectors.

01:08:34.005 --> 01:08:35.880
So what you can see is
